### --- Variables ---
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@railwayUrl = https://listing-agent-api-production.up.railway.app
@adminAuth = Basic admin:randoPass3243!**

### Get all listings (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/listings

### Get listing 1 — check the amenityScores field
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/listings/1

### Search active listings, first 5
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/listings/search?status=Active&size=5

### Bbox search (map view) — Twin Cities metro
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/listings/search?minLat=44.85&maxLat=45.10&minLng=-93.45&maxLng=-93.10

### === AMENITY SCORING (Phase 4 admin endpoints) ===

### Trigger full batch refresh — returns 202 immediately, work happens in background
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/scoring/refresh-all
Authorization: {{adminAuth}}

### Synchronously recompute one listing (5-15 seconds wait)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/scoring/listings/7
Authorization: {{adminAuth}}

### Verify scores populated
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/listings/1

### === CRUD with auth ===

### Create a new listing (will trigger async scoring after save)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/listings
Authorization: {{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mlsId": "TEST-001",
  "status": "Active",
  "listDate": "2026-06-04",
  "listPrice": 750000,
  "address": "123 Main St",
  "city": "Minneapolis",
  "zipCode": "55401",
  "beds": 3,
  "bathsFull": 2,
  "latitude": 44.9778,
  "longitude": -93.2650
}

// NorthstarMLS Demo

### ─── MLS GRID DEMO ─────────────────────────────────────────────
@mlsGridDemoUrl = https://api-demo.mlsgrid.com/v2
@mlsGridToken = 03c7efa16339fc79dc710eea89c63ae5350728d5

### 1. Pull metadata — shows all OriginatingSystemName values you have access to
GET {{mlsGridDemoUrl}}/$metadata
Authorization: {{mlsGridToken}}

### 2. Check which MLSs are in this demo subscription
###    MlgCanView=true filters to live/displayable records only
GET {{mlsGridDemoUrl}}/Property?$select=OriginatingSystemName&$top=50&$filter=MlgCanView eq true
Authorization: {{mlsGridToken}}

### 3. Once you know the OriginatingSystemName for NorthstarMLS (probably 'northstar' or 'mnnorthstar'),
###    pull one record with everything expanded
GET {{mlsGridDemoUrl}}/Property?$filter=OriginatingSystemName eq 'northstar' and MlgCanView eq true&$top=1&$expand=Media,Rooms
Authorization: {{mlsGridToken}}

### 4. If northstar doesn't work, try these variants:
GET {{mlsGridDemoUrl}}/Property?$filter=OriginatingSystemName eq 'nstar' and MlgCanView eq true&$top=1
Authorization: {{mlsGridToken}}

### 5. Pull raw metadata for NorthstarMLS specifically — field definitions
GET {{mlsGridDemoUrl}}/$metadata?$filter=OriginatingSystemName eq 'northstar'
Authorization: {{mlsGridToken}}